  "text": "Having established the informativeness of the various NE types, in this section, we examine the impact of NEs and their hidden location information for geolocation. To extract the hidden location information of each NE, we collect the locations of all tweets in our tweet corpus that contain that Table 4 : Accuracy and distance results for various methods. -indicates no report in respective paper NE. To divide the world into regions with roughly the same number of users, we use a k-d tree approach proposed by [CITATION_1] . As a result, we will cover larger regions when the population density is low and vice versa. Each region is then considered as a label to train the classifiers. The approach of using k-d tree is also used in [CITATION_2] ; [CITATION_3] and [CITATION_4] . See Table 3 for an example of the following methods. All use logistic regression as classifier, following [CITATION_5] .",
